Special Coverage Arab Cup FIFA Qatar 2025
programme.desc: The second edition of the FIFA Arab Cup is scheduled to be held in Qatar from December 1 to 18, 2025. The tournament will be hosted across six venues, all of which were utilized during the FIFA World Cup™ three years prior. As with Qatar 2022, Al Bayt Stadium will host the tournament's opening match, while the prestigious Lusail Stadium will serve as the venue for the final. Stay updated with comprehensive coverage of the Arab Cup Qatar 2025 on BeIN Sports News.

programme.desc: The FIFA Arab Cup Qatar 2025 has successfully revived the vibrant festival atmosphere reminiscent of the World Cup in Qatar. The tournament has been transformed into an accessible, family-friendly public celebration through the implementation of large-scale fan zones, cultural activations, efficient transportation, and strategic promotions. programme.desc: The FIFA Arab Cup Qatar 2025 has successfully revived the vibrant festival atmosphere reminiscent of the World Cup in Qatar. The tournament has been transformed into an accessible, family-friendly public celebration through the implementation of large-scale fan zones, cultural activations, efficient transportation, and strategic promotions. A key element of this success is the establishment of numerous high-profile fan hubs, providing supporters with engaging spaces to gather well before kick-off.
